    <extendedTextInteraction format="plain" responseIdentifier="RESPONSE11">
      <prompt>You have read two stories about Buster Bear: "Buster Bear Goes Fishing" and "A Surprising Thing Happens." Write an essay explaining how the events in both stories are the <strong>same</strong> and <strong>different</strong>. <br/> In your writing be sure to include a topic sentence, details from the story to support your explanation, and a concluding sentence. <br/></prompt>
    </extendedTextInteraction>
    <rubricBlock class="sample_response" view="author proctor scorer testConstructor tutor">
      <ul> <li>In the informative/explanatory response, students should include details from the text to highlight the similarities and differences of the events from both passages. </li> <li>Similarities include: recurring characters, common theme of fear, same setting, both told through narrator point of view</li> <li>Differences include: a few new characters in " A Surprising Thing Happens," different events, lack of dialogue from Buster Bear in "A Surprising Thing Happens." and his character is shown to be scared versus being a bully.  </li> </ul>
